title: Man accused of trying to reverse Trump's election defeat pleads guilty
description: A man accused of trying to reverse Donald Trump's election defeat in Georgia has pleaded guilty.

title: Italy wants migrant rescue ships sent back to countries funding their operation
description: Rescue ships run by charities that pick up migrants at sea should be returned to the countries funding them, Italy's foreign minister has said.

title: France grapples with bed bug infestation as authorities warn of health problem before Olympics
description: France is grappling with a bed bug problem, with the government warned it must tackle the pests ahead of the Olympics in Paris.

title: US urges India to cooperate with probe into killing of Sikh separatist in Canada
description: US secretary of state Antony Blinken has urged India to cooperate with an investigation into the assassination of a Sikh separatist on Canadian soil.

title: Cleverly praises Trump's foreign affairs record and his 'surprisingly effective' style
description: The foreign secretary has praised Donald Trump's record in foreign affairs as the former president remains the frontrunner for the republican nomination for president in the 2024 election.

title: UEFA bosses point to Ukraine's softening stance to calm unease over Russia decision
description: European football chiefs will seek to quell a rift over the ending of the blanket ban on Russian teams by highlighting how Ukraine's government ended its outright opposition to their athletes competing against Russians appearing as neutrals, Sky News understands.

title: Taoiseach weighs in on Gymnastics Ireland row after young black gymnast denied medal at event
description: Taoiseach Leo Varadkar has said there is no room for racism in sport, after controversy around a young black gymnast not receiving a medal at a presentation ceremony.

title: More than three quarters of Nagorno-Karabakh's population flees to Armenia
description: More than three-quarters of Nagorno-Karabakh's population has fled to Armenia.

title: Longest-serving US female senator dies
description: California senator Dianne Feinstein - known for being a vocal advocate of gun control measures - has died aged 90.

title: Suspect in Rotterdam gun rampage suffered from 'psychotic behaviour'
description: A medical student suspected of shooting dead three people in Rotterdam had a history of psychotic behaviour, according to prosecutors.

title: Ex-president's daughter accused of running multi-million dollar crime ring
description: The daughter of Uzbekistan's former president has been indicted on charges including money laundering and bribery after being accused of running a huge multi-million dollar crime network known as "The Office".

title: Manchester United player Antony to return to duties despite abuse allegations
description: Manchester United footballer Antony will resume training at the club and will be available for selection despite abuse allegations being brought against him.

title: Elon Musk wades into debate on immigration as he visits Mexico border
description: Elon Musk has decided to wade into the US immigration debate.

title: Police check on Britney Spears after video of her dancing with knives
description: Authorities have reportedly carried out a welfare check on Britney Spears after the popstar shared a video of herself dancing with knives at home.

title: Man who shot YouTube prankster acquitted
description: A man who shot a YouTube prankster who followed him around a shopping centre food court has been found not guilty by a US jury.

title: Napoli insist they 'never intended to make fun' of own striker in TikTok video
description: Italian champions Napoli have insisted they did not intend to offend striker Victor Osimhen after appearing to mock him in a video on TikTok.

title: At least 52 killed and dozens injured in suicide bombing in Pakistan
description: At least 52 people have been killed and dozens more have been injured in a suicide bomb attack in Pakistan, officials have said.

title: Military could help tackle 'unprecedented' surge in violence in Sweden
description: Sweden's prime minister has summoned the head of its armed forces to help police stem a surge in gang-related shootings and bombings.

title: Fast food workers cry and cheer as minimum wage increased to $20 an hour in California
description: Fast food workers in California will receive a minimum wage of $20 (£16.36) from next year.
